<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"h-what-is-a-hexagon">What is a hexagon=
?</h2>



<p>We know that a hexagon is a polygon formed with six sides and six <a hre=
f=3D"https://helpingwithmath.com/adding-and-subtracting-angles/" data-inter=
nallinksmanager029f6b8e52c=3D"49" title=3D"Adding and Subtracting Angles">a=
ngles</a>. Also, in a regular hexagon, there are six symmetrical lines and =
it has <a href=3D"https://helpingwithmath.com/rotational-symmetry/" data-in=
ternallinksmanager029f6b8e52c=3D"376" title=3D"Rotational Symmetry">rotatio=
nal symmetry</a> of order of 6.</p>



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"how-do-we-find-the-area-of-a-hexagon">=
How do we find the area of a hexagon?</h2>



<p>When we talk of the area of the hexagon we mean to consider the space th=
at is confined within the sides of the polygon. The area of a hexagon is ca=
lculated by using the following formula =E2=80=93</p>



<p>Area of a hexagon =3D $\frac{(3=E2=88=9A3)}{2}$ s<sup>2</sup></p>



<p>where =E2=80=9C s =E2=80=9C is the side of a regular hexagon.</p>



<p>Let us understand the formula using an example.</p>



<p><strong>Example</strong></p>



<p>Suppose, we wish to find the area of a hexagon having a side of 4 cm</p>



<p><strong>Solution</strong></p>



<p>We have been given that we have a hexagon that has a side of 4 cm. Now, =
we already know that the area of a hexagon is given by Area of a hexagon =
=3D $\frac{(3=E2=88=9A3)}{2}$ s<sup>2</sup> , where, =E2=80=9C s =E2=80=9C =
is the side of a regular hexagon.</p>



<p>If we substitute =E2=80=9C s=E2=80=9D in the above equation by 4, which =
is the length of a side of our regular hexagon, we will have,</p>



<p>Area of a hexagon =3D $\frac{(3=E2=88=9A3)}{2}$ 4<sup>2</sup></p>



<p>=E2=87=92 Area of a hexagon =3D$\frac{(3=E2=88=9A3)}{2}$ x 4 x 4</p>



<p>=E2=87=92 Area of a hexagon =3D 3=E2=88=9A3 x 8</p>



<p>Now, the value of =E2=88=9A3 =3D 1.732</p>



<p>Substituting this value of =E2=88=9A3 in the above equation, we will hav=
e,</p>



<p>Area of a hexagon =3D 3 x 1.732 x 8</p>



<p>=E2=87=92 Area of a hexagon =3D 41.568 sq. cm</p>



<p><strong>Therefore, the area of the hexagon having a side of 4 cm will be=
 41.568 sq. cm =3D 41.57 sq. cm</strong></p>



<p>How can we use the hexagon calculator to perform this operation? Let us =
find out.</p>



