<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"how-to-find-the-area-of-a-hexagon-when=
-are-given-its-perimeter">How to find the area of a hexagon when are given =
its perimeter?</h2>



<p>In order to find the area of a hexagon when are given its perimeter, we =
need to first understand the formula of the perimeter of the hexagon.</p>



<p>The perimeter of a hexagon =3D 6 x s, where, =E2=80=9C s =E2=80=9C is th=
e side of a regular hexagon.</p>



<p>Let us understand it using an example.</p>



<p>Suppose we have a hexagon having the side 4 cm. what would be its perime=
ter?</p>



<p>The perimeter of the hexagon would be given by 6 x Side =3D 6 x 4 =3D 24=
 cm.</p>



<p>Now, let us see how we can use this formula to find the area of a hexago=
n.</p>



<p>We know that</p>



<p>Area of a hexagon =3D $\frac{(3=E2=88=9A3)}{2}$ s<sup>2</sup> =E2=80=A6=
